.TH SPM\-REPO\-SIGN 8 "June 2026" "spm 0.1.0" "System Manager's Manual"
.SH NAME
spm\-repo\-sign \- Sign a repository Release file with the configured key
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B spm repo sign
\fIname\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
Sign a repository's Release file using the Ed25519 keypair previously
generated with \fBspm repo gen-key\fR.
.P
The signing process creates the following files depending on the
repository format:
.TP
Native repositories
\fBRelease.sig\fR \(em detached signature for the \fBRelease\fR file.
.TP
Apt repositories
\fBRelease.sig\fR \(em detached signature, and \fBInRelease\fR \(em clearsigned
Release file (signature embedded inline).
.TP
DNF repositories
\fBrepomd.xml.asc\fR \(em ASCII-armored detached signature for
\fBrepodata/repomd.xml\fR.
.P
The repository is automatically signed after each \fBspm repo publish\fR
if a signing key is configured.  This command is only needed for
re-signing after manual changes to the repository metadata.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
\fIname\fR
The name of the repository whose Release file should be signed.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP \(bu 2
\fBspm repo sign myrepo\fR
Sign the Release file of the \fImyrepo\fR repository.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR spm (8),
.BR spm\-repo\-gen\-key (8),
.BR spm\-repo\-publish (8)
